 MBOMBELA – The Lowveld will be experiencing severe thunderstorms this afternoon, according to the South African Weather Service. The weather utility has issued warnings to that effect, indicating which areas are most likely to be affected. ALSO READ: Water crisis looms if taps run dry A weather warning was also issued to Gauteng and Limpopo’s residents who will also be experiencing adverse weather conditions, following a week of extremely hot weather. The MEC for cooperative governance and traditional affairs, Speedy Mashilo, warned communities to avoid power lines and disaster units across the province are on high alert in case of any emergencies arising from the expected thunderstorms.